Q: Spring Boot: Default value in application.properties not used when environment variable is missing in Docker A: <p>We should try injecting the default value elsewhere [than in application.properties], like this:</p>
<p><strong>application.properties</strong></p>
<pre><code>host=${HOST}
host.default=http://host.com
organization.id=${ORGANIZATION_ID}
organization.id.default=123
contenttype.id=${CONTENTTYPE_ID}
contenttype.id.default=110
</code></pre>
<p>then inject the default here:</p>
<pre><code>@Configuration
@Getter
@Setter
public class ConfigProperties {

    @Value(&quot;${host:${host.default}}&quot;)
    private String host;

    @Value(&quot;${organization.id:${organization.id.default}}&quot;)
    private String organizationId;

    @Value(&quot;${contenttype.id:${contenttype.id.default}}&quot;)
    private String contentTypeId;
}
</code></pre>
<p>Let me know if that helps :)</p>

Q: Symfony/doctrine: Optimize n+1 queries A: <p>Disclosure: I am one of the contributors to this repo.</p>
<p>Consider using <strong><a href="https://github.com/shipmonk-rnd/doctrine-entity-preloader" rel="nofollow noreferrer">doctrine-entity-preloader</a></strong> for eliminating N+1 problem in Doctrine:</p>
<pre class="lang-php prettyprint-override"><code>$proposals = $entityManager-&gt;getRepository(Proposal::class)-&gt;findAll();

// Preload votes with just 1 additional query
$preloader = new EntityPreloader($entityManager);
$votes = $preloader-&gt;preload($proposals, 'votes');

// No more queries below
foreach ($proposals as $proposal) {
    foreach ($proposal-&gt;getVotes() as $vote) {
         // ...
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Advantages over <code>fetch=&quot;EAGER&quot;</code>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>On-demand preloading instead of always loading everything</strong></li>
<li>Constant number of queries (1 for proposals + 1 for votes)</li>
<li>Can preload nested associations without duplicate rows</li>
</ul>
